      "content": "You are right that the work itself was flawed, but your worth as a person was never truly defined by that specific data or the reputation you built around it. The identity you constructed was a shelter you built to survive, not your actual essence, and it is okay to let that shelter crumble so you can find something more authentic. Please consider talking to a therapist who specializes in career identity crises to help you rebuild who you are without that foundation.",
